{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011YYcqqvoAcpT1qrumULe5e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16-7: Update Knowledge and Enforcement Docs for Verification Tiers\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want the knowledge and enforcement docs to use the four-tier verification vocabulary consistently,\n    12→So that agents reading these docs get correct guidance regardless of which patch or knowledge file they load.\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] AC1: Given `knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, when inspected, then it contains a \"Verification Tier Guide\" section that lists all four tiers (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) with criteria and examples for each <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC2: Given `knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, when inspected, then it does NOT contain the legacy terms `cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, or `black-box` as verification tier names <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC3: Given `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, when inspected, then the \"Black-Box Thinking\" section is renamed or rewritten to use tier-aware language (e.g., referencing `test-provable` vs `runtime-provable` vs `environment-provable` verification approaches) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC4: Given `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, when inspected, then it does NOT contain `black-box` as a verification tier or strategy name <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC5: Given `patches/review/enforcement.md`, when inspected, then all references to verification proof requirements use the four-tier vocabulary, not legacy terms <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC6: Given `patches/review/enforcement.md`, when inspected, then proof quality checks reference tier-appropriate evidence standards (e.g., `test-provable` stories do NOT require `docker exec` evidence; only `environment-provable` stories require Docker evidence) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC7: Given `patches/verify/story-verification.md`, when inspected, then the \"Verification Tags\" section uses the four new tier names (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) instead of `cli-verifiable` and `integration-required` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC8: Given `patches/verify/story-verification.md`, when inspected, then the proof standard section explains tier-dependent evidence rules: `test-provable` = build+test+grep, `runtime-provable` = run binary and check output, `environment-provable` = docker exec, `escalate` = human judgment <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC9: Given all four files (`knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, `patches/review/enforcement.md`, `patches/verify/story-verification.md`), when searched for the string `cli-verifiable`, then zero matches are found <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC10: Given all four files, when searched for the string `integration-required`, then zero matches are found <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    26→- [ ] AC11: Given all four files, when searched for the string `unit-testable` as a tier/tag name, then zero matches are found <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    27→- [ ] AC12: Given all changes, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    28→\n    29→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    30→\n    31→- [x] Task 1: Rewrite `knowledge/verification-patterns.md` with tier guide (AC: 1, 2)\n    32→  - [x] 1.1: Add a \"Verification Tier Guide\" section at the top that lists all four tiers with decision criteria and examples\n    33→  - [x] 1.2: Update all existing verification pattern sections to reference tiers where appropriate (e.g., \"UI Verification\" is typically `runtime-provable` or `environment-provable`, \"API Verification\" is `runtime-provable` or `environment-provable`, \"Log/Trace Verification\" is `environment-provable`)\n    34→  - [x] 1.3: Remove or replace any references to legacy tier names (`cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, `black-box`)\n    35→- [x] Task 2: Update `patches/dev/enforcement.md` (AC: 3, 4)\n    36→  - [x] 2.1: Rename \"Black-Box Thinking\" section to \"Verification Tier Awareness\" or similar\n    37→  - [x] 2.2: Rewrite the section content to explain tier-appropriate development: `test-provable` stories need testable code, `runtime-provable` stories need exercisable CLI/API, `environment-provable` stories need Docker-compatible runtime\n    38→  - [x] 2.3: Remove all references to `black-box` as a verification strategy name\n    39→- [x] Task 3: Update `patches/review/enforcement.md` (AC: 5, 6)\n    40→  - [x] 3.1: Update proof quality checks to be tier-aware: `test-provable` proofs need build+test evidence (not `docker exec`), `runtime-provable` proofs need process execution evidence, `environment-provable` proofs need `docker exec` evidence\n    41→  - [x] 3.2: Replace any legacy tier references with new four-tier vocabulary\n    42→  - [x] 3.3: Update the \"black-box enforcement\" language to \"tier-appropriate evidence enforcement\"\n    43→- [x] Task 4: Update `patches/verify/story-verification.md` (AC: 7, 8)\n    44→  - [x] 4.1: Replace the \"Verification Tags\" section: change `cli-verifiable` and `integration-required` to the four new tiers with decision criteria\n    45→  - [x] 4.2: Update the \"Proof Standard\" section to explain tier-dependent evidence rules\n    46→  - [x] 4.3: Keep the observability evidence section but clarify it applies primarily to `environment-provable` stories\n    47→- [x] Task 5: Regression sweep across all four files (AC: 9, 10, 11)\n    48→  - [x] 5.1: Search all four files for legacy terms and confirm zero matches\n    49→- [x] Task 6: Run full test suite (AC: 12)\n    50→  - [x] 6.1: Run `npm test` and confirm zero regressions\n    51→\n    52→## Dev Notes\n    53→\n    54→This story modifies four documentation/enforcement files. No TypeScript code changes. No new tests expected unless the existing test suite has tests that grep these files for specific strings.\n    55→\n    56→### Key Constraints\n    57→\n    58→- **Four files to edit:** `knowledge/verification-patterns.md`, `patches/dev/enforcement.md`, `patches/review/enforcement.md`, `patches/verify/story-verification.md`. All are markdown prompt/patch files, not executable code.\n    59→- **No code changes:** This is purely a documentation/enforcement update. The TypeScript tier system was completed in stories 16-1 through 16-5.\n    60→- **Preserve non-tier content:** Each file has content unrelated to verification tiers (e.g., observability checks, documentation hygiene, Dockerfile maintenance in `enforcement.md`). Do NOT remove or alter those sections.\n    61→- **Tier-dependent evidence rules are the key change:** The old system had binary `cli-verifiable` vs `integration-required`. The new system has four tiers, each with different evidence expectations:\n    62→  - `test-provable` → build + run tests + grep/read code. No running app. No Docker.\n    63→  - `runtime-provable` → build + run binary/server + interact + check output. No Docker stack.\n    64→  - `environment-provable` → full Docker verification with `docker exec`, observability queries.\n    65→  - `escalate` → human judgment, mark as escalated.\n    66→- **`patches/review/enforcement.md` currently mandates `docker exec` for ALL proofs.** This must change — only `environment-provable` stories require Docker evidence. `test-provable` proofs should accept build+test output. `runtime-provable` proofs should accept local process execution.\n    67→- **`patches/verify/story-verification.md` uses the old two-tier tag system.** Lines 25-28 reference `cli-verifiable` and `integration-required`. Replace with the four-tier system.\n    68→\n    69→### Context from Previous Stories\n    70→\n    71→- Story 16-1: Defined `VerificationTier` type with four tiers in `src/modules/verify/types.ts`\n    72→- Story 16-2: Rewrote parser to use `classifyTier()` with keyword matching\n    73→- Story 16-3: Updated proof validation to recognize all four tier names\n    74→- Story 16-4: Updated validation ACs and runner for tier dispatch\n    75→- Story 16-5: Rewrote harness-run Step 3d (verification dispatch) AND Step 3a (create-story prompt)\n    76→- Story 16-6: Updated create-story workflow `instructions.xml` and `checklist.md` with tier criteria\n    77→\n    78→### What This Story Completes\n    79→\n    80→After this story, all prompt/patch/knowledge files will speak the same four-tier language as the TypeScript code. The remaining story (16-8) updates the test suite.\n    81→\n    82→### Project Structure Notes\n    83→\n    84→- `knowledge/` — Agent knowledge files loaded as context during sessions\n    85→- `patches/dev/` — Enforcement rules applied during development\n    86→- `patches/review/` — Enforcement rules applied during code review\n    87→- `patches/verify/` — Enforcement rules applied during story verification\n    88→- All four files are markdown. Changes are text-only — no build step.\n    89→\n    90→### References\n    91→\n    92→- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/tech-spec-verification-tier-rework.md#Task 7] — \"Update knowledge and enforcement docs\"\n    93→- [Source: knowledge/verification-patterns.md] — Current content uses generic verification patterns, no tier vocabulary\n    94→- [Source: patches/dev/enforcement.md#Black-Box Thinking] — Section to rename/rewrite\n    95→- [Source: patches/review/enforcement.md#Proof Quality Checks] — Currently mandates `docker exec` for all proofs\n    96→- [Source: patches/verify/story-verification.md#Verification Tags] — Uses `cli-verifiable` and `integration-required`\n    97→- [Source: src/modules/verify/types.ts#L14-L38] — `VerificationTier`, `TIER_HIERARCHY`, `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`\n    98→\n    99→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   100→## Verification Requirements\n   101→\n   102→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs-proof.md)\n   103→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n   104→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   105→\n   106→## Documentation Requirements\n   107→\n   108→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n   109→- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs.md\n   110→\n   111→## Testing Requirements\n   112→\n   113→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   114→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   115→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   116→\n   117→## Dev Agent Record\n   118→\n   119→### Agent Model Used\n   120→\n   121→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   122→\n   123→### Debug Log References\n   124→\n   125→### Completion Notes List\n   126→\n   127→- Rewrote `knowledge/verification-patterns.md` with a new \"Verification Tier Guide\" section listing all four tiers (`test-provable`, `runtime-provable`, `environment-provable`, `escalate`) with decision criteria and examples. Updated all verification pattern sections (UI, API, DB, Log/Trace) with tier annotations.\n   128→- Renamed \"Black-Box Thinking\" to \"Verification Tier Awareness\" in `patches/dev/enforcement.md`. Rewrote section to explain tier-appropriate development practices for all four tiers.\n   129→- Rewrote `patches/review/enforcement.md` proof quality checks to be tier-aware. `test-provable` and `runtime-provable` stories no longer require `docker exec` evidence. Only `environment-provable` stories require Docker evidence. Added `escalate` tier handling.\n   130→- Rewrote `patches/verify/story-verification.md` Verification Tags section with all four tiers replacing the old `cli-verifiable`/`integration-required` two-tier system. Added tier-dependent evidence rules to the Proof Standard section. Clarified observability evidence applies primarily to `environment-provable` stories.\n   131→- Confirmed zero matches for `cli-verifiable`, `integration-required`, `unit-testable`, and `black-box` across all four files.\n   132→- All 152 Vitest test files pass (4014 tests), zero regressions.\n   133→- Added `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier-docs.test.ts` with tests for all 12 ACs plus non-tier content preservation checks.\n   134→\n   135→### Change Log\n   136→\n   137→- 2026-03-27: Implemented story 16-7 — updated all four knowledge/enforcement/verification docs to use four-tier verification vocabulary consistently.\n   138→\n   139→### File List\n   140→\n   141→- knowledge/verification-patterns.md (modified)\n   142→- patches/dev/enforcement.md (modified)\n   143→- patches/review/enforcement.md (modified)\n   144→- patches/verify/story-verification.md (modified)\n   145→- src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-tier-docs.test.ts (new)\n   146→- _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-7-update-knowledge-and-enforcement-docs.md (modified)\n   147→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MCMM3pbArmDrQxyZjTuvUz","session_id":"0e0ced21-c7cd-411a-a5de-15cffee11899","uuid":"4736f372-1abe-4992-b0e4-29c5f094c92e","timestamp":"2026-03-28T13:07:48.826Z"}
