u exhausted all automated approaches? Is there genuinely no way to verify this without a human or external paid service? Only then use `escalate`. This tier is rare.\n    41→75:Typically `runtime-provable` or `environment-provable` depending on whether the UI requires a Docker stack.\n    42→107:Typically `runtime-provable` (local server) or `environment-provable` (Docker-hosted service).\n    43→131:Typically `environment-provable` — requires a running database instance.\n    44→149:Typically `environment-provable` — requires the observability stack running in Docker.\n    45→```\n    46→<!-- /showboat exec -->\n    47→\n    48→---\n    49→\n    50→## AC 2: knowledge/verification-patterns.md does NOT contain legacy terms\n    51→\n    52→**Verdict:** PASS\n    53→\n    54→<!-- showboat exec: verify AC2 — zero matches for legacy tier names -->\n    55→```bash\n    56→grep -c \"cli-verifiable\\|integration-required\\|unit-testable\\|black-box\" knowledge/verification-patterns.md\n    57→```\n    58→\n    59→```output\n    60→0\n    61→```\n    62→<!-- /showboat exec -->\n    63→\n    64→---\n    65→\n    66→## AC 3: patches/dev/enforcement.md \"Black-Box Thinking\" renamed to tier-aware language\n    67→\n    68→**Verdict:** PASS\n    69→\n    70→<!-- showboat exec: verify AC3 — section renamed to Verification Tier Awareness -->\n    71→```bash\n    72→grep -n \"Verification Tier Awareness\" patches/dev/enforcement.md\n    73→```\n    74→\n    75→```output\n    76→38:### Verification Tier Awareness\n    77→```\n    78→<!-- /showboat exec -->\n    79→\n    80→<!-- showboat exec: verify AC3 — references test-provable and runtime-provable and environment-provable -->\n    81→```bash\n    82→grep -n \"test-provable\\|runtime-provable\\|environment-provable\" patches/dev/enforcement.md\n    83→```\n    84→\n    85→```output\n    86→40:- **`test-provable` stories** need testable code: pure functions, clear inputs/outputs, assertions that can run via `npm test`.\n    87→41: